Setting Up the Project Locally

Install Backend Dependencies:
First, navigate to the backend directory and install the necessary dependencies.

bash
Copy
cd backend
npm install
Install Frontend Dependencies:
Next, navigate to the frontend directory and install the dependencies.

bash
Copy
cd frontend
npm install
Run the Backend and Frontend Locally:
Start the backend:

bash
Copy
cd backend
npm start
The backend server will be running at http://localhost:8080.

Start the frontend:

bash
Copy
cd frontend
npm start
The frontend React app will be running at http://localhost:3000.

Now, you should be able to access the app on your local machine:

Backend: http://localhost:8080
Frontend: http://localhost:3000
